## How many wards are singing new hymns each week?

The following plot shows the number of new hymns sung per ward each week since the release of the new hymns.


::: {.cell}
::: {.cell-output-display}
![](index_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-4-1.png){width=624}
:::
:::


There are far more zeros than I expected. The first week saw the most number of new hymns, but even then it was only about a third of wards. Since then only about a quarter of wards have sung new hymns on a given Sunday. 





However, a lot of my data comes from single-week contributions from various wards, so just just because a ward didn't sing a new hymn this week doesn't mean they haven't done any yet. To see what proportion of wards have introduced new hymns up to this point, I took a look at the 30 wards that I have data from from every week since the first batch of hymns came out. About a quarter of them haven't sung new hymns at all yet. About half have sung three new hymns. The most was one ward that has sung a new hymn five out of six weeks so far. 


## What hymns are most popular?

It should come as no surprise that the most popular hymn in this new batch is <hymn>Come, Thou Fount of Every Blessing (#1001)</hymn>. But just how popular is it? 





